In .NET 10 (and late .NET 9), Android's `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` is fully deprecated. MAUI now uses **edge-to-edge** rendering with `WindowInsets`-based layout. Here's how to fix it:

## 1. Use `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` (simplest)

MAUI enables this by default. If you disabled it, re-enable it in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.UseMauiApp<App>()
    .ConfigureMauiHandlers(handlers =>
    {
#if ANDROID
        Microsoft.Maui.Platform.KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Connect();
#endif
    });
```

## 2. If that's insufficient — handle padding via `Keyboard` insets

In your page or a custom handler, react to inset changes. In your `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Controls.Platform;

// In OnCreate, after base call:
WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window, false);

ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(
    Window.DecorView.FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content),
    new InsetsListener());

class InsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        // imeInsets.Bottom is the keyboard height in px
        v.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, imeInsets.Bottom);
        return insets;
    }
}
```

## 3. Ensure your layout cooperates

Wrap your chat UI so the input bar is at the bottom of a `Grid` or `VerticalStackLayout` inside a `ScrollView`-free container:

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*,Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}" />
    <Entry Grid.Row="1" Placeholder="Type a message..." />
</Grid>
```

**TL;DR:** Option 1 (KeyboardAutoManagerScroll) handles most cases automatically. If your layout is complex or you're using edge-to-edge, go with Option 2 to manually respond to IME insets.
